cs.CL, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.RO 

This paper deals with the task of vision and language navigation, which involves natural language processing, computer vision, and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves computer vision techniques, such as image processing and feature extraction, which makes cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) another likely category. The paper also proposes a novel training paradigm that leverages multiple instructions, which involves machine learning techniques, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a likely category. The paper also involves parameter sharing and generalization, which are topics in machine learning, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. Finally, the paper deals with navigation in a physical environment, which involves robotics and control, making cs.RO (Robotics) a possible category.
